  "prompt": "What is FARC?",
  "response": "FARC, which stands for the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (Spanish: Fuerzas Armadas Revolucionarias de Colombia), is a Marxist-Leninist guerrilla group that was founded in 1964. Initially formed as a response to social inequality and political exclusion in Colombia, FARC sought to establish a communist state through armed struggle.\n\nThe group engaged in various activities, including guerrilla warfare, drug trafficking, and kidnappings, which it used to finance its operations and exert control over certain regions of Colombia. Over the decades, FARC became one of the most prominent and enduring insurgent organizations in Latin America.\n\nIn recent years, FARC undertook a peace process with the Colombian government, culminating in a historic peace agreement signed in 2016. This agreement led to the disarmament of many FARC members and the transformation of the group into a political party, now known as the Common Alternative Revolutionary Force (also abbreviated as FARC). \n\nHowever, the implementation of the peace agreement has faced various challenges, including violence against former combatants and lingering tensions in the country. The legacy of FARC and the conflicts surrounding its history continue to influence Colombian society and politics.",
